Given a ResetAction targeting a (From, To) edge, the algorithm must record an EdgeResolution with the current endpoint hashes, then collapse all nodes whose every edge is either consistent or has a matching resolution entry. Collapse updates the baseline hash to the current scan hash and prunes resolutions for collapsed edges. When a node's scan hash is empty string (deleted), collapse removes the node entirely and filters out its edges. The target edge must be in baseline (in either direction) or the action errors. The returned EvaluatedState propagates Edges and Resolutions unchanged. See principles.friction for why reset is per-edge.